      <body>
         <!-- please fill out the template below, replacing text in square brackets with the actual information -->
         <head>
            <title>Witness Statement Provided by [NAME]</title> 
            <date>[DATE OF STATEMENT]</date>
            <orgName>[FOR WHOM THE STATEMENT WAS GIVEN (POLICE, CORONER, DA)]</orgName>
         </head>
         <!-- Ellie Luciani -->
         <div type="segment" n="1">
            <byline><persName ref="#luciani">Ellie Luciani</persName></byline>
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>During the time in <placeName>the east</placeName> there, when he <persName
                  ref="#taylor_william">(Taylor)</persName> was directing her
                  <persName ref="#minter_mary">(Mary)</persName>, did you observe any awakening of a friendship or
                  love between the two of them?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab> No.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>When did you first see that, or did you at all?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>I never did know it, Mr. Keyes, until <persName ref="#mott_john"> Mr.
                  Mott</persName> told me of the <objectName type="communication"
                     >letters</objectName> that had been found in <persName ref="#taylor_william">Taylor's</persName>
                  <objectName type="furniture"> drawer</objectName> that absolutely is convincing that there had been
                  something there.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>You mean after he was killed?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>Yes, and <persName ref="#eyton_charles">Mr Eyton</persName> told me also after <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr.
                  Taylor</persName> was killed that he knew that, that he knew for a long time
                  that <persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary</persName> and <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor</persName> had been
                  intimate, and I said then <quote>"<persName ref="#eyton_charles">Mr. Eyton</persName> you should have
                     told me"</quote></ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>During that time, <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">Mrs. Shelby</persName> (referring to latter part of
                  <date>1919</date> and early part of <date>1920</date>), was
                  <persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary</persName> going around with <persName ref="#taylor_william">Taylor</persName> to your
                  knowledge at all?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>Why no, and <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor</persName> was the most perfectly poised man,
                  such a proper man. He would take <persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary</persName> out to dinner and he
                  would invariably invite me and my mother to go to dinner with them.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Did you make any objections?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab> Not the least in the world.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Were you friendly with him?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>Oh, yes. **</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Do you remember anyone in particular with whom she was associating at that
                  time?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>It wasn't men. Men hadn't begun to give me any trouble at that time. It was
                  women.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Who was that?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab><persName>Jeannie McPherson.</persName></ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab><persName ref="#taylor_william">Taylor's</persName> name never entered into the discussion then?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>No. I always felt that, when <persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary</persName> was out with <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr.
                  Taylor</persName> she was under a good influence. **</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Did you ever have any words with <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor</persName> over
                  <persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary</persName>?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>Never a word, never the slightest word. (Speaking of the time <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">Mrs.
                  Shelby</persName> went to <persName ref="#taylor_william">Taylor's</persName>
                  <placeName>home</placeName> at <time>2 a.m.</time> looking for
                  <persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary</persName>) </ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Did this secretary of yours, <persName>Miss Whitney</persName>, go in the
                  <placeName>house</placeName> with you?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>No, I know she didn't because there was nobody in the <placeName>room</placeName>
                  but <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor</persName> and me. She stayed in the
                  <objectName type="vehicle">car</objectName>.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Did you have any <objectName type="weapon">weapon</objectName> with you at that time?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>Good lord, no.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>You are sure you didn't have a <objectName type="weapon">revolver</objectName> with you?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>No, <persName>Mr. Keyes.</persName></ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Well, you owned a <objectName type="weapon">revolver</objectName> at that time?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab> No. If I owned a <objectName type="weapon">revolver</objectName> at that time, I don't know
                  where it was. It was thrown away.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>What date was it when you were at <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor's</persName> home that you
                  were telling about?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>I think I could almost fix that date, <persName>Mr. Keyes</persName>, referring
                  to a certain little <objectName type="miscellaneous">book</objectName>, you know. Because I was reading
                  <persName ref="#minter_mary"> Mary's</persName>
                  <objectName type="miscellaneous">diary</objectName> and she goes on to say in this
                  <objectName type="miscellaneous">diary</objectName> that she and I had some little words that
                  <time>evening</time>, you see, and she has written it very cleverly, about the
                  small girl going out in a huff, etc., and she adds that mother was right. ** And I
                  think the date of that happening is right in her
                  <objectName type="miscellaneous">diary</objectName>.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Did you ever make a threat to kill <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor?</persName></ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>No, <persName>Mr. Keyes.</persName> I never had any reason or desire to kill
                  <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor.</persName></ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>And you are positive, are you,<persName ref="#shelby_charlotte"> Mrs. Shelby</persName>, that you never
                  at any time threatened <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor?</persName></ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>Certainly not, I had no reason. I never threatened to shoot <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr.
                  Taylor</persName>. I don't think I ever threatened to shoot any man.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>To shoot him? No, because I had no reason. I had no provocation. I never had a
                  quarrel with <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor</persName> in my life.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>You spoke of having thrown a <objectName type="weapon">gun</objectName> away?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>No, my mother did that.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>That was your <objectName type="weapon">gun</objectName>?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>The <objectName type="weapon">gun</objectName> was given to me in <placeName>Santa
                  Barbara</placeName> by <persName>Harry Eaves</persName>, who has a
                  <placeName>jewelry shop</placeName> up there - a very short little
                  <objectName type="weapon">pistol</objectName> - a little <objectName type="weapon">automatic</objectName> -
                  ** and he said to me, <quote>"I have got two and you ought to have
                     one."</quote></ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Where did you say you shot it once?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>I got a friend of mine to take me out in <placeName>Santa Barbara</placeName>,
                  just off the <objectName type="miscellaneous">road</objectName>, and we shot it into a
                  <placeName>bank</placeName> and I shot it once.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <!-- Patrick Mannion -->
         </div>

<!-- Patrick Mannion -->
         <div type="segment" n="2">
            <byline><persName ref="#mannion">Patrick Mannion</persName></byline>
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Did you ever do any target practice with it?</ab>
            </sp>
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>Yes, that one <time>time</time>. It was enough for <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">me</persName>. The
                  thing was too short. <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">I</persName> can shoot a <objectName type="weapon">long
                     pistol</objectName>. <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">I</persName> wouldn't mind shooting a
                  <objectName type="weapon">shot gun.</objectName> **</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp>
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab> Well, <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">Mrs. Shelby</persName>, <persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary</persName> shot that
                  <objectName type="weapon">pistol</objectName> off one <time>time</time>, didn't
                  <persName ref="#minter_mary">she</persName>?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp>
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>Yes, she shot it off twice.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Was that the "suicide"?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>That's the "suicide". (re supposed suicide) "Well, we were living at
                  <placeName>56 Fremont Place. </placeName> ** I remember the
                  <roleName ref="#whitney_charlotte">secretary</roleName> was there that <time>night</time>,
                  <persName ref="#whitney_charlotte">Miss Whitney.</persName> ** <persName ref="#minter_mary">She (Mary)</persName> rushed up
                  the <objectName type="furniture">steps</objectName> crying "I am going to end it all. I am going to
                  end it all." ** Then <persName ref="#whitney_charlotte">Charlotte (Miss Whitney)</persName> said to me,
                  "Mes. Shelby, oh, Mrs. Shelby, there's a <objectName type="weapon">pistol</objectName> in your
                  <objectName type="furniture">closet</objectName>." ** But she ran up the
                  <objectName type="furniture">stairs</objectName> and ran in my room and closed the
                  <objectName type="furniture">door</objectName>.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab> Did she look the <objectName type="furniture">door</objectName>?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>Oh, locked the <objectName type="furniture">door</objectName>, and the first thing we knew - bang.
                  ** and a second more and - bang - the second shot. ** <persName>The
                     <roleName ref="#eaton_chauncy">chauffeur</roleName> (Chauncey Eaton)</persName> appeared, and the
                  <persName>night watchman</persName> (?), and I said, "Break in the door". The
                  two men rushed against the <objectName type="furniture">door</objectName>, the <objectName type="furniture">door</objectName> fell in, and there lay <persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary</persName> on my
                  bedroom floor. ** They picked her up so tenderly, and
                  <persName ref="#eaton_chauncy">Chauncey</persName> turned her over and he said, "Why, <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">Mrs.
                     Shelby</persName>, there is no blood on her." ** By that time the
                  <persName ref="#whitney_charlotte">secretary</persName> had faded out of the picture in a faint ** and
                  she (<persName ref="#miles_juliet">Mrs. Shelby's mother, Mrs. Miles</persName>) said,"Why no, she is
                  not shot; stand her up, <persName ref="#eaton_chauncy">Chauncey</persName>." ** Then she
                  (<persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary</persName>) looked at us and said, "I thought I would give you
                  all a jolt."</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>** was there anything said about <persName ref="#taylor_william">Taylor</persName> in that? Did he have
                  anything to do with that quarrel?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp>
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>No, I don't think he had anything to do with that ** I may have asked her if she
                  had been out with <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor</persName>.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp>
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>But there was no <name type="event">quarrel</name> about <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor</persName>?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp>
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>It seems to me she mentioned <persName ref="#taylor_william">Taylor's</persName> name. I don't remember
                  now, or what. **</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp>
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Then the <objectName type="miscellaneous">report</objectName> that I got that you have been practicing
                  some <objectName type="weapon">revolver</objectName> shooting - is there anything to that?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp>
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>I told you I shot it once. I know a man who will verify it - <persName ref="#stockdale_carl">Mr.
                  Stockdale</persName>.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab> No other <objectName type="weapon">pistol</objectName> at any other <time>time</time>?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>No, I am afraid of <objectName type="weapon">pistols</objectName>. **</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>What did your <persName ref="#minter_mary">mother</persName> do with your
                  <objectName type="weapon">pistol</objectName> after <persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary</persName> pulled this
                  stunt?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>That was all there was to it. Of course, we found <persName ref="#whitney_charlotte">Charlotte
                  Whitney</persName> in a faint on the <placeName type="#furniture">floor</placeName> and we had to
                  revive her. ** And <persName ref="#eaton_chauncy">Chauncey</persName> was trying to find out where the
                  <objectName type="accessories">bullets</objectName> went, and we discovered one
                  <objectName type="accessories">bullet</objectName> had been shot into my
                  <objectName type="furniture">closet</objectName>, and we found that, and another one went up in
                  the ceiling of the <objectName type="furniture">closet</objectName>. I remember
                  <persName ref="#minter_mary">mother</persName> taking the <objectName type="weapon">pistol</objectName>. She
                  said, "Here, give me that. That's enough of <objectName type="weapon">pistols</objectName> lying
                  around."</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>What did she do with it?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>I never saw it again. I think I asked her once or twice what she did with it, and
                  she said,"It's out. It's put away."</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <ab> ---</ab>
            
            <sp>
               <speaker>MRS. SHELBY:</speaker>
               <ab>I had an engagement with a man the <time>next morning (2-2-22) at 9
                  o'clock</time>. *** This man was a client of a friend of my daughter's,
                  <persName ref="#reiner">Mr. Albert Reiner.</persName> *** I also had been talking to a man
                  about buying an <objectName type="weapon">Aeolian Organ</objectName>, and he stopped 1n<time>
                     that morning</time> And while these two men were in the room, the
                  <objectName type="accessories">telephone</objectName> rang. It was then a <time>little after
                     9</time>, and <persName ref="#stockdale_carl">Mr. Carl Stockdale</persName> called me up. He had gone
                  to the <placeName>studio</placeName> to work and had learned of the death of
                  <persName ref="#taylor_william">William Desmond Taylor</persName>. Naturally, knowing that he
                  directed <persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary</persName>, he called me up and told me that
                  <persName ref="#taylor_william">William Desmond Taylor</persName> bad been found dead that
                  <time>morning</time>.</ab>
            </sp>
         </div>
         
         <!-- Jack Murphy -->
         <div type="segment" n="3">
            <byline><persName ref="#murphy">Jack Murphy</persName></byline>
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><orgName>POLICE</orgName></speaker>
               <ab>Just what did he tell you?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="shelby">MRS. SHELBY</persName></speaker>
               <ab>He said, "<persName ref="shelby">Mrs. Shelby</persName>, I just wanted to call you
                  up and tell you. I am at the <placeName>studio</placeName>. <persName ref="taylor"
                     >William Desmond Taylor</persName> was found dead <time>this morning</time>."
                  "Oh," I said, "that's terrible." That's all he knew. ** I turned to these gentlemen
                  and said, "Oh, my, it's terrible. A man who directed <persName ref="minter">my
                     daughter</persName>, a very charming gentleman, was found dead <time>this
                        morning</time>." ** In a few minutes the <objectName type="furniture"
                           >telephone</objectName> rang again. ** This time <persName ref="berger">Miss
                              Berger</persName> said, "<persName ref="taylor">William Desmond Taylor</persName>
                  was murdered this morning. He was shot." I said, "Oh, my, this is terrible; the man
                  was murdered? Was shot?" So we discussed that and the organ man knew I was waiting to
                  go out with <persName ref="rice">Mr. Rice</persName> so ** <persName ref="rice">Mr.
                     Rice</persName> and I got in his <objectName type="vehicle">car</objectName> **
                  and I said, "<persName ref="rice">Mr. Rice</persName>, do you mind if I stop at my
                  <objectName>house</objectName> and tell my people?" ** and it seems to me that on
                  the way crossing <placeName>Vermont</placeName> I met my mother coming over in a
                  <objectName type="vehicle">car</objectName> with the <persName role="chauffeur"
                     >chauffeur</persName> and I just waved to her to turn around and come on back with
                  us. I remember that distinctly. ** I was in a great hurry because <persName
                     ref="rice">Mr. Rice</persName> was waiting for me in front, and I remember the
                  chauffeur had parked my <objectName type="vehicle">blue Packard</objectName> in the
                  <placeName>driveway</placeName>, and something was said about <persName
                     ref="minter">Mary</persName> wanted the <objectName type="vehicle"
                        >car</objectName>. <persName ref="eaton">Chauncey</persName> had gone to get
                  <persName ref="minter">Mary's</persName>
                  <objectName type="vehicle">car</objectName>. However, I went
                  <placeName>upstairs</placeName> in a great hurry, and I said, "Oh, <persName
                     ref="ivers">Julia</persName>, dear, <persName ref="taylor">Mr. Taylor</persName>
                  was murdered last night." She said, "Oh, it isn't possible. I can't believe it. It
                  isn't true." I said, "Oh, yes, it is. <persName ref="berger">Miss Berger</persName>
                  told me so." **</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><orgName>POLICE</orgName></speaker>
               <ab>Did <persName ref="woolwine">Mr. Woolwine</persName> ever try to take your
                  statement?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="shelby">MRS. SHELBY</persName></speaker>
               <ab>No, he never asked me a thing, <persName ref="keyes">Mr. Keyes</persName>. Nobody
                  ever questioned me.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="mott">MR. MOTT</persName></speaker>
               <ab> Tell <persName ref="keyes">Mr. Keyes</persName> exactly now, that part of the
                  conversation with <persName ref="eaton">Chauncey</persName>?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="shelby">MRS. SHELBY</persName></speaker>
               <ab> I said, "<persName ref="eaton">Chauncey</persName>, what did you tell them?" He
                  said, "I told them that you called me up very early that morning, about <time>half
                     past seven</time>, and my wife said you went over there without breakfast; that
                  you wanted to go over to the <placeName>Hobart house</placeName>." I said, "The
                  morning of the <persName ref="taylor">Taylor</persName> murder?" He said, "Yes." I
                  said, "Why, I couldn't have known until after <time>9 o'clock</time>." He said that
                  he drove me over that morning and said that I was at the window with the <objectName
                     type="miscellaneous">papers</objectName>. I said, "How could that be; besides
                  there wasn't any papers <time>that morning</time>." "No," he said, "that's what they
                  told me down at <placeName>the office</placeName>, that there wasn't any <objectName
                     type="miscellaneous">papers</objectName> that early." I said, "Well, that's
                  nothing, it is just a lapse of memory, it is of no consequence." And finally he saw
                  he was in the wrong. I explained to him that <persName ref="rice">Mr. Rice</persName>
                  had driven me over.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="mott">MR. MOTT</persName></speaker>
               <ab> Now explain that <persName ref="blue">Monte Blue</persName> proposition.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="shelby">MRS. SHELBY</persName></speaker>
               <ab> (<persName>Mrs. Shelby</persName> tells about some night when <persName
                  ref="minter">Mary</persName> had failed to come <placeName>home</placeName>, and
                  they had looked for her until about <time>2:30 a.m</time>. and finally located her
                  <objectName type="vehicle">car</objectName> in front of <placeName><persName
                     ref="whitney">Charlotte Whitney's</persName> house</placeName>) So <persName
                        ref="margaret">Margaret</persName> and I rushed in and went up the steps hurriedly
                  and opened the door and came upon <persName ref="minter">Mary</persName> and
                  <persName ref="blue">Monte Blue</persName> on the couch. The door opened right
                  into the <placeName>front room</placeName>. This <persName ref="blue">Monte
                     Blue</persName> started to run out into the <placeName>kitchen</placeName> and out
                  the <placeName>back door</placeName>.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><orgName>POLICE</orgName></speaker>
               <ab> You mean that they were in a compromising position?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="shelby">MRS. SHELBY</persName></speaker>
               <ab> Yes. I was about the maddest woman that could ever be. I grabbed this halfbreed
                  Indian by his shirt tail and I said, "Come right back in <placeName>this
                     room</placeName>. I have something very forceful to say to you. Come back
                  here."</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="davis">MR. DAVIS</persName></speaker>
               <ab> That time she went out with <persName ref="neilan">Marshall Neilan</persName>,
                  after the murder; wasn't that about <date>two nights afterward</date>?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="shelby">MRS. SHELBY</persName></speaker>
               <ab>Yes.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><orgName>POLICE</orgName>
               </speaker>
               <ab>Immediately afterwards, wasn't it?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="shelby">MRS. SHELBY</persName>
               </speaker>
               <ab> It was.</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="keyes">MR. KEYES</persName>
               </speaker>
               <ab> She tried to kill you, you say?</ab>
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="shelby">MRS. SHELBY</persName></speaker>
               <ab> Yes. ** Oh, <persName ref="minter">Mary</persName> said around the house freely,
                  <quote>"Oh, <persName ref="shelby">Mrs. Shelby</persName> killed <persName
                     ref="taylor">Taylor</persName>"</quote>. Not only once but many times. She was
                  always saying that.</ab>
            </sp>
         </div>

